==English==

===Etymology===
{{wikipedia}}
From Greek petros, [[stone]] + ichor (the blood in the veins of Greek Gods) (rock-essence). The term was coined by two Australian researchers in 1964 for an article in the journal Nature. 

===Noun===
'''petrichor'''
#The [[scent]] of [[rain]] on [[dry]] [[earth]]; more specifically, it is the name of the yellow [[organic]] [[oil]] that yields this scent.